76 SECTION 2. Section 228 of said chapter 111 of the General Laws, as appearing in the
77 2022 Official Edition, is hereby amended by striking out subsection (e) and inserting in place
78 thereof the following subsection:-
79 (e) A health care provider shall determine if it participates in a patient’s health benefit
80 plan prior to said patient’s admission, procedure or service for conditions that are not emergency
81 medical conditions as defined in section 1 of chapter 176O. If the health care provider does not
82 participate in the patient’s health benefit plan and the admission, procedure or service was
83 scheduled more than 7 days in advance of the admission, procedure or service, such provider
84 shall notify the patient verbally and in writing of that fact not less than 7 days before the
85 scheduled admission, procedure or service. If the health care provider does not participate in the
86 patient’s health benefit plan and the admission, procedure or service was scheduled less than 7
87 days in advance of the admission, procedure or service, such provider shall notify the patient
88 verbally of that fact not less than 2 days before the scheduled admission, procedure or service or
89 as soon as is practicable before the scheduled admission, procedure or service, with written
90 notice of that fact to be provided upon the patient’s arrival at the scheduled admission, procedure
91 or service. If a health care provider that does not participate in the patient’s health benefit plan
92 fails to provide the required notifications under this subsection, or if the provider is rendering
93 unforeseen out-of-network services, as defined in subsection (a) of section 30 of chapter 176O,
94 the provider shall not bill the insured except for any applicable copayment, coinsurance or
95 deductible that would be payable if the insured received the service from a participating health
96 care provider under the terms of the insured’s health benefit plan. Nothing in this subsection
97 shall relieve a health care provider from the requirements under subsections (b) to (d), inclusive.
